The paper deals with the problem of text indexing, which is a fundamental algorithmic problem in computer science. The paper presents a new solution for on-line indexing, which involves constructing a suffix tree on-line. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of maintaining a dynamic list under insertions, deletions, and order queries, which suggests that it may also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper also presents an efficient data structure for solving the Predecessor search on Dynamic Subsets of an Ordered Dynamic List problem, which suggests that it may belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category. The paper also deals with the Order-Maintenance Problem, which suggests that it may belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents bounds for several applications, including fully-persistent arrays, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
